goals.1: Identify the BGP for tennis player
goals.2: Identify the BGP for tennis tournament
goals.3: Return the four Grand Slam of tennis (hint: One of these four is Wimbledon) (the result set must be a list of four couples Grand Slam IRI and label).
goals.4: Find the three different type of possible surfaces in a tennis court (the result set must be a list of three couples surface IRI and label).
goals.5: Return the tournaments played in the 2018 Wimbledon Championships edition with the related winners (hint: men and women do not play together, there are two distinct tournament ) (the result set must be a list of elements with tournament IRI and label, and winner IRI and label).
goals.6: Consider the tennis players born after 1975, return who won more Grand Slams and cut the result to the top-10 (the result set must be a list of triples player IRI, label and #victories).
goals.7: Consider the country for sport property of the tennis player (NO Country of citizenship). Return the countries with at least one player who won at least one edition of each Grand Slam (the result set must be a list of country IRI and label).
goals.8: Consider the country for sport property of the tennis player (NO Country of citizenship). Return the countries with at least one player who was ranked 1 in the tennis ranking  (the result set must be a list of country IRI and label).

find the property date of birth
see the properties of the instances of the Grand Slam
6.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?prop ?name WHERE { wd:Q1426 ?prop ?x. ?prop sc:name ?name. FILTER(REGEX(?name,"birth")). }

6.narrative: see the properties of the instances of the Grand Slam
6.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?people ?name COUNT(?tournament) AS ?win WHERE { ?x wdt:P361 wd:Q102113. ?edition wdt:P31 ?x. ?tournament wdt:P361 ?edition. ?tournament wdt:P1346 ?people. ?people wdt:P569 ?birth. ?people sc:name ?name. FILTER (year(?birth) > 1975). } GROUP BY ?people ?name ORDER BY DESC (?win) LIMIT 10

7.narrative: find the property country for sport
7.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?prop ?name WHERE { wd:Q1426 ?prop ?x. ?prop sc:name ?name. FILTER(REGEX(?name,"sport")). }

7.narrative: see the properties of the instances of the Grand Slam
7.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?people ?name COUNT(DISTINCT ?x) AS ?win WHERE { ?x wdt:P361 wd:Q102113. ?edition wdt:P31 ?x. ?tournament wdt:P361 ?edition. ?tournament wdt:P1346 ?people. ?people wdt:P1532 ?country. ?people sc:name ?name. } GROUP BY ?people ?name HAVING (COUNT(DISTINCT ?x) >3 )

7.narrative: see the properties of the instances of the Grand Slam
7.query: SELECT ?country ?name COUNT(DISTINCT ?people) AS ?people WHERE{ ?people wdt:P1532 ?country. { SELECT ?people COUNT(DISTINCT ?x) AS ?win WHERE { ?x wdt:P361 wd:Q102113. ?edition wdt:P31 ?x. ?tournament wdt:P361 ?edition. ?tournament wdt:P1346 ?people. } GROUP BY ?people HAVING (COUNT(DISTINCT ?x) >3 ) } ?country sc:name ?name. } GROUP BY ?country ?name

8.narrative: see the properties of the instances of the Grand Slam
8.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?country ?name WHERE { ?people wdt:P1532 ?country; wdt:P1352 ?ranking; wdt:P106 wd:Q10833314. ?country sc:name ?name. FILTER(?ranking = 1) } GROUP BY ?country ?name
